{"word":"H8302 - שִׁרְיֹון - shiryôwn - shir-yone' - Breastplate","slug":"H8302","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שִׁרְיֹון</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shiryôwn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shir-yone'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Breastplate"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05D9;&#x05E0;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05D9;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05D9;&#x05DF;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05D9;&#x05D5;&#x05DF; - shiryo&#x0302;n  shirya&#x0302;n  shirya&#x0302;h  shiryo&#x0302;na&#x0302;h</b> - <i>(shir) -yone', -yawn', -yaw', -yo-naw'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H8281\">H8281</a> in the original sense of <i>turning</i>; a <i>corslet</i> (as if <i>twisted</i>): - breastplate, coat of mail, habergeon, harness. See <a href=\"#/H5030\">H5030</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8287\">H8287</a>, <a href=\"#/H8298\">H8298</a>"}]}